Well...

514
00:31:02,975 --> 00:31:08,331
Fabia's probably still a little
sensitive about the accident.

515
00:31:08,698 --> 00:31:10,273
Accident?

516
00:31:10,287 --> 00:31:12,640
Oh, you didn't know.

517
00:31:12,778 --> 00:31:17,772
About a month ago, she backed her S.U.V.
into 12 people outside Marquee.

518
00:31:18,197 --> 00:31:20,233
I was in Saint-Tropez.

519
00:31:20,248 --> 00:31:21,842
I had no idea.

520
00:31:21,855 --> 00:31:24,561
Why--why didn't
anyone say anything?

521
00:31:24,576 --> 00:31:28,543
Daniel, if I may,
you didn't include me in the concept.

522
00:31:28,556 --> 00:31:31,262
And we all thought you
knew what you were doing.

523
00:31:33,108 --> 00:31:37,893
Fabia's not just talking about
canceling... the "Mode" supplement.

524
00:31:37,908 --> 00:31:44,300
She's considering... Pulling advertising 
from every single one of my magazines.

525
00:31:44,927 --> 00:31:47,432
Is it true you worked
on this on your own,

526
00:31:47,447 --> 00:31:49,321
didn't consult Wilhelmina
or anyone else?

527
00:31:49,337 --> 00:31:50,653
Look, I can explain.

528
00:31:50,668 --> 00:31:54,833
I had--I had a very strong feeling
she was trying to sabotage me.

529
00:31:55,286 --> 00:31:58,720
The only person who
sabotaged you was yourself.

530
00:31:58,738 --> 00:32:00,333
Sorry I let you down.

531
00:32:00,348 --> 00:32:03,900
Well, I'm sorry I keep hoping you'll
be something you're clearly not.

532
00:32:03,918 --> 00:32:06,381
- My leg is cramping.
- Look, I can fix this.

533
00:32:06,398 --> 00:32:08,431
I'll just present her
with a whole new idea.

534
00:32:08,445 --> 00:32:09,971
We just closed book.
It's too late.

535
00:32:09,986 --> 00:32:12,810
Tomorrow morning. Please.

536
00:32:13,537 --> 00:32:15,233
Give me another chance.

537
00:32:15,248 --> 00:32:17,982
Daniel called again
looking for you.

538
00:32:18,538 --> 00:32:22,451
What part of "unavailable"
does he not understand?

539
00:32:22,468 --> 00:32:24,561
I'll let him know.

540
00:32:26,516 --> 00:32:29,293
He really should've
come to me earlier.

541
00:32:29,488 --> 00:32:33,372
It wouldn't have made any
difference now, would it?

542
00:32:33,387 --> 00:32:35,240
Not really.

543
00:32:36,216 --> 00:32:37,721
To teamwork.

544
00:32:37,737 --> 00:32:39,633
To revenge.

545
00:33:32,626 --> 00:33:34,710
He has a heart condition.

546
00:33:34,726 --> 00:33:37,271
Yes, he--he needs
his medication.

547
00:33:37,288 --> 00:33:42,351
But you can't just cover the pills
and then randomly decide to stop.

548
00:33:42,738 --> 00:33:46,773
But it's--it's a real person's health,
it's not a case number.

549
00:33:46,787 --> 00:33:49,572
Give me the phone.
I'll let 'em have it.

550
00:33:49,877 --> 00:33:53,402
No. No, I don't wanna hold again.
Not again.

551
00:33:53,657 --> 00:33:55,601
No, just wait--

552
00:34:00,585 --> 00:34:04,242
It's fine. We'll just--
we'll get 'em tomorrow. It's fine.

553
00:34:04,256 --> 00:34:05,930
Thank you, mi amor.

554
00:34:05,947 --> 00:34:08,832
You're so much better at dealing with
this bureaucratic stuff than I am.

555
00:34:08,845 --> 00:34:10,491
No, you know I don't mind.

556
00:34:10,507 --> 00:34:11,760
I know.

557
00:34:11,776 --> 00:34:13,543
You're always so good to me.

558
00:34:13,555 --> 00:34:17,870
So strong,
determined, optimistic...

559
00:34:19,346 --> 00:34:21,702
just like your mother was.

560
00:34:28,548 --> 00:34:30,733
Why haven't you
returned my calls?

561
00:34:30,745 --> 00:34:31,702
I've been busy.

562
00:34:31,716 --> 00:34:35,272
Betty, I need to talk to you.
I made a terrible mistake.

563
00:34:35,285 --> 00:34:38,921
Wait, did you realize this
before or after Gina dumped you?

564
00:34:38,937 --> 00:34:41,123
What? No, no,
I broke up with her.

565
00:34:41,136 --> 00:34:45,923
Betty, it was wrong,
and I wanna make this up to you. I--

566
00:34:46,156 --> 00:34:47,862
Betty.

567
00:34:48,026 --> 00:34:49,443
Are you dating someone?

568
00:34:49,456 --> 00:34:51,732
Walter, please go!

569
00:34:51,748 --> 00:34:53,240
Dating this guy?

570
00:34:53,258 --> 00:34:55,431
Look, you need to go.
Please. You need to go.

571
00:34:55,447 --> 00:34:57,051
But, Betty, I-I...

572
00:34:58,928 --> 00:35:00,743
What are you doing here?

573
00:35:00,758 --> 00:35:02,500
I wanna talk.

574
00:35:06,145 --> 00:35:08,212
It's a nice place.

575
00:35:08,227 --> 00:35:11,553
Yeah, we're just in
between interior designers.

576
00:35:11,565 --> 00:35:13,360
- Really?
- No.

577
00:35:13,375 --> 00:35:16,103
Oh, right. It's a joke.

578
00:35:17,866 --> 00:35:20,451
Betty, I am so sorry.

579
00:35:20,985 --> 00:35:23,882
You didn't deserve what
I put you through.

580
00:35:24,498 --> 00:35:29,153
I-I listened to all the wrong people
about a lot of things, and...

581
00:35:29,198 --> 00:35:31,842
I have no one to
blame but myself.

582
00:35:34,386 --> 00:35:37,311
Well, I appreciate
that, Daniel.

583
00:35:37,465 --> 00:35:39,720
But you're going to leave here,

584
00:35:39,738 --> 00:35:42,793
and you're going to take your
town car back to your soho loft,

585
00:35:42,808 --> 00:35:44,572
and I'm still gonna be here--

586
00:35:44,587 --> 00:35:45,972
out of work

587
00:35:45,985 --> 00:35:49,073
and dealing with problems
that you'll never understand.

588
00:35:49,085 --> 00:35:51,922
Try me.
Betty, come on, we've all got problems.

589
00:35:51,937 --> 00:35:53,993
Oh, and what are yours, Daniel,

590
00:35:54,005 --> 00:35:58,252
what restaurant you're gonna eat at,
which model you're gonna sleep with?

591
00:35:58,267 --> 00:36:02,351
Try spending the day on the
phone with some crappy H.M.O.,

592
00:36:02,365 --> 00:36:04,561
getting them to cover
your dad's prescriptions.

593
00:36:04,578 --> 00:36:07,752
Or try lining up
a job--any job--

594
00:36:07,766 --> 00:36:10,551
'cause you have to help
pay the rent next month.

595
00:36:10,565 --> 00:36:12,201
Look...

596
00:36:12,807 --> 00:36:15,683
I lost a brother a while back.

597
00:36:15,696 --> 00:36:20,161
He was the good one in our family,
and I've never quite measured up.

598
00:36:20,175 --> 00:36:22,062
But I am trying.

599
00:36:22,876 --> 00:36:26,710
Betty, I--I could never
compare my problems to yours,

600
00:36:26,727 --> 00:36:28,671
but they're mine.

601
00:36:29,028 --> 00:36:31,350
Nothing's ever easy.

602
00:36:35,716 --> 00:36:39,142
I saw the layout
you made for Fabia.

603
00:36:39,357 --> 00:36:40,913
You did?

604
00:36:40,926 --> 00:36:43,250
I thought it was very smart

605
00:36:43,267 --> 00:36:45,401
and beautiful.

606
00:36:45,597 --> 00:36:47,383
Well, thank you.

607
00:36:47,396 --> 00:36:50,662
I want to take your
ideas to Fabia,

608
00:36:50,675 --> 00:36:52,963
giving you credit, of course.

609
00:36:53,338 --> 00:36:57,182
And I really want you to come back,
be my assistant.

610
00:36:57,196 --> 00:37:00,350
I promise you things
will be different.

611
00:37:01,316 --> 00:37:06,232
I--Daniel, I--I mean,
I-I really have to think about that.

612
00:37:09,207 --> 00:37:12,250
Well... you have tonight,

613
00:37:12,267 --> 00:37:15,763
otherwise, I'll probably
be out of a job as well.

614
00:37:35,026 --> 00:37:36,601
Did you hear that?

615
00:37:39,125 --> 00:37:40,931
Every word.

616
00:37:47,506 --> 00:37:51,281
So... where the hell is he?

617
00:37:51,297 --> 00:37:53,343
He said 10:00 a.m.

618
